      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;I like the idea of the opposing factions and the related progressive storyline.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I think it's a wise decision that the rewards are equal, or at least equivalent. If they weren't, people would complain incessantly.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I don't think that the current faction setup is prohibitive or extraordinarily annoying. As has been mentioned, a Cazic Thule following SK friend of mine is currently at the same stage as me in Norrath's Keepers progress. He was caught up a week into the expansion. Even if he plays more than you... what will it take, a month to be in a position to reap all of the benefits of alliance with a faction, while earning reasonably good experience, tokens for reasonably good loot, and having fun? That's a lot more fun than grinding in Kael for indeteriminate amounts of time, or watching people slaughter innumerable helpless Coldain. And really, that's the best comparison I can make for faction, beucase it's the last time faction mattered for crap as far as I can tell. Personally, I thought the faction setup in Qeynos was the best, but that model has long since been abandoned; since Velious, the closest things to faction we've had have been Traders of the Haven (running inane delivery tasks) and Dranik Loyalists (endless grinding!). I prefer this setup. And I think that in the time spent expressing discontent over it on the boards, you probably could have gotten a Stillmoon Population Control Task, done a Stillmoon group mission, and - if you pick the right mission - gotten a faction hit from a kill in there, as well.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;We may have grown spoiled from having faction not matter at all in PoP, LoY, LDoN, and only be required for specific tasks in GoD and OoW. With DoN, it matters again. You can take advantage of the options available to work with that, or you can complain that, because of your chosen path in EQ,&amp;nbsp;you have to work at it a little more than some of your friends. I know which seems like more fun to me.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
