      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;If they've figured out how to prevent duping, I wish SOE would go ahead and&amp;nbsp;release a small patch to fix crystals (make them tradable as they were intended to be). The longer crystals remain&amp;nbsp;no-drop, the more people give up their desired faction and go with the opposite, simply because most of their friends/guildmates are on that faction and they're accumulating crystals they cannot use. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;For example, the Dark faction folks in my guild are much more avid mission-goers; they're doing 4-5 times the number of missions as the folks on&amp;nbsp;Keeper faction, so most of the groups available to me are doing Dark missions, hence most of the crystals I'm&amp;nbsp;earning are Ebon. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I'd already have enough to buy&amp;nbsp;an augment I *really* want, but those crystals are useless to me because I cannot trade them for Radiants. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;This faction/crystal system was designed in such a way that players shouldn't feel like they're being separated from friends and guildies because of faction.... but with the crystals not being tradable, that&amp;nbsp;design consideration&amp;nbsp;is largely wasted.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;People don't want to earn savings bonds and post-dated gift certificates they can't use for weeks. They want to earn crystals that they can &lt;U&gt;spend&lt;/U&gt;. So most will only do missions from their own faction -- and the separation that SOE devs went out of their way to avoid, is happening anyway.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
